article.headline: High Point 72, Radford 67
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Danny Gathings scored 22 points and pulled down eight rebounds to help High Point hang on to beat Radford 72-67 on Saturday. Javier Palacios added 14 for the Panthers (12-5, 5-1 Big South Conference), who were held without a field goal for a little more than six minutes to end the game. Whit Holcomb-Faye, the leading scoring in the conference, had 25 points, 22 in the second half after being held to 1-of-9 shooting in the opening period. He made 5-of-11 3-point attempts. Olumuyiwa Popoola scored 16, while Chris Oliver added 13 for the Highlanders (6-9, 2-3). High Point led 31-19 at the half after holding Radford of 22 percent shooting from the floor.
